1. Definitions
“Software” refers to the EchOS operating system project, including all code, logic, assets, scripts, packaged builds, unpackaged builds, and documentation.
“Copyright Holders” refers to RoboLabs LLC and Echo Inc.
“Developer” refers to any individual granted explicit written permission by the Copyright Holders to modify the Software.
“User” refers to any individual using the Software without developer permissions.
“Redistribution” refers to sharing, uploading, publishing, distributing, or making the Software available in any form.

2. Grant of Rights
2.1 Personal and Commercial Use
Users are permitted to:
• Use the Software for personal purposes.
• Use the Software for commercial purposes.
• View and study the source code.
No fees or royalties are required for these uses.

2.2 Developer Modification Rights
Modification of the Software is only permitted for Developers who have received explicit written authorization from the Copyright Holders.
Authorized Developers may:
• Modify the Software.
• Create derivative works.
• Use modified versions privately.
Developers may not redistribute modified versions unless separately authorized.

3. Restrictions
3.1 Unauthorized Modification Prohibited
Users who are not authorized Developers may not:
• Modify the Software.
• Alter or remove copyright notices.
• Bypass, disable, or interfere with anti‑tamper or integrity systems.
• Reverse‑engineer, unpack, or decompile the Software beyond what is permitted by law.

3.2 Redistribution Restrictions
Users may not redistribute:
• The Software in any form.
• Modified or unmodified copies.
• Packaged or unpackaged versions.
• Derivative works.
Redistribution requires explicit written permission from RoboLabs LLC or Echo Inc.

Redistributed versions, when permission is granted, must be provided at no cost.
No redistributed version may be sold, monetized, or offered behind a paywall.

3.3 No Misrepresentation
Users may not:
• Claim authorship of the Software.
• Present modified versions as official.
• Use the names RoboLabs LLC, Echo Inc., or EchOS for endorsement without permission.

4. Ownership
The Software is the exclusive property of RoboLabs LLC and Echo Inc.
All rights not expressly granted in this license are reserved.

5. Integrity and Anti‑Tamper
The Software may include:
• Anti‑tamper systems.
